  "metadata": {
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Adding support for languages and regions"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Add the language and region combinations you want to support to your project. For",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "each localization, select the resources, such as image and audio files, that you",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "want to localize.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Add-localizations",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Add localizations",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In the project editor, select the project name under Project, and click Info. Under",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Localizations, click the Add button (+), then choose a language and region combination",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "from the pop-up menu.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "adding-support-for-languages-and-regions-1",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The pop-up menu contains the language name followed by the language ID in parentheses",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "— for example, German (de), Japanese (ja), and Arabic (ar). For regional variants",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and scripts, the region appears in parentheses followed by the language ID in parentheses—",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "for example, English (India) (en-IN) where en-IN is the language ID. The Other submenu",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "(at the bottom of the menu) contains additional languages and regions to choose from.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For guidance, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.Xcode/documentation/Xcode/choosing-localization-regions-and-scripts",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "adding-support-for-languages-and-regions-2",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you have localizable resources in the project, select the resource files that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "you want to localize in the sheet that appears, and click Finish. For example, select",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "images, audio, strings, and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".stringsdict",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " files that you add to your project.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For storyboard and XIB interfaces, select the user interface files (files with a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".storyboard",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".xib",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " filename extension). Xcode adds a strings file to the localization",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "folder that contains the text to translate, as well as comments that describe the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "user interface components. For example, if you add German to an iOS app that uses",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "storyboards, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "LaunchScreen.storyboard",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " becomes a group containing a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "LaunchScreen.storyboard (Base)",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "LaunchScreen.strings (German) ",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": "file.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Xcode adds the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "Base",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " and the development language to the localization table",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "by default. Use the Base localization for resources that support string substitution",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "at runtime, such as storyboard, XIB, and Siri intent definition files.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "View-localizable-resources",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "View localizable resources",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can verify the resources for each localization in the Project navigator and Finder.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The first time you add a localization, Xcode changes every resource that you want",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to localize into a group containing the original file and a localization-specific",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "version. The next time you add a localization, Xcode adds another localization-specific",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "file to the group.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "adding-support-for-languages-and-regions-3",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In the file system, Xcode creates a separate localization folder to store the localization-specific",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "resources. The name of the folder is the language ID followed by the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".lproj",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " file",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "extension — for example, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "de.lproj ",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": "if you choose German (de) from the localization",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "menu.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
